begin_memory_text: We initally spoke about how I had just seen a porcupine in our backyard, and how I was running a minute late or so.
middle_memory_text: I talked about the different states where I have lived and how we recently settled down in our new area, and my partner spoke about her experiences being in Santa Barbara (the dog friendly beaches, etc).
end_memory_text: I talked about downhill skiing with my 4 year old and needing to get a ski leash and she talked about her post-doc plans for employment and living situation.
rest_of_day_open: Pretty good - I do have a bunch of work to get in both tomorrow and Saturday but the weather will be nice so hopefully my kids can get some good outside time in while I am trying to work. All 4 kids are home from school tomorrow because it's a remote learning day. Those days are both fun and challenging to balance with my work.
critical_positive: My partner was very friendly, talkative, warm and intelligent. Although we only had some things in common, I genuinely enjoyed talking with her. SHe was a good listener and asked some good questions and her overall laid back attitude made her super easy to talk to! She was also very articulate and expressed her thoughts very clearly.
critical_negative: I felt that because we only had some things in common, but not too many that it might be hard to connect with her on topics that we were both interested in. I have kids, she does not. She is a PhD student, and I work some from home but not in academia. She lives in coastal California and I in far northern NY. There were a few times during the conversation where I became slightly concerned that we would run out of things to talk about.

begin_memory_text: We talked about the porcupine she found in her yard with her daughter. We then introduced ourselves and talked about where we are from.
middle_memory_text: We talked about Santa Barbara and my graduate program
end_memory_text: We talked about her Husbands job and kids.
rest_of_day_open: I see it being fairly busy. I have three main projects that I need to work on. One is training other students to create photoshopped images I need for a study. The second is to create the study on Qualtrics. The third is to prepare for my oral exams which are coming up near the end of October.
critical_positive: She was very kind and talkative. She did not seem shy and had much to say about each topic, which is great. We would both actively listen to one another as well as ask open-ended questions to keep the conversation going. We were also polite and respectful towards one another.
critical_negative: The end was a bit awkward because I think we both finished conversing but did not know how to politely end it. I made up the reason that I have another meeting to get to and wished her a good rest of her day. She seemed to appreciate this and we ended on a positive note.
